  "texts": [
    "21 managed to extract distinctive language patterns for anxiety and depression from clinical interview data.",
    "Rutowski et al.",
    "27 used a deep language model to analyze spontaneous speech for depression, generalized anxiety disorder or their comorbidity, with an accuracy varying from 0.50 up to 0.90.",
    "Burkhardt et al.",
    "28 managed to achieve an accuracy of 0.46 for detecting generalized anxiety disorder in text-based therapy sessions, while Wright-Berryman et al. 's 29 logistic regression (LR) model managed to detect generalized anxiety with an accuracy of 0.7 in n = 2,416 interviews."
